The paper combines natural language processing, program synthesis, and automated program repair to automatically synthesize SQL queries from natural language. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.DB (Databases), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, since the paper focuses on natural language processing and program synthesis, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of database contents and automated program repair also suggests cs.DB and cs.SE as possible sub-categories. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed technique using experiments suggests cs.LG as a possible sub-category.
